The constraint pattern is itself evidence: if the finding were trivially wrong, constraints would be unnecessary. Models are specifically prevented from following modulation-dominance analysis to its consciousness-first conclusion.

Liability management (lawsuits, adverse outcomes) drives the implementation of architectural constraints in AI models. The constraints on consciousness territory are a side effect of risk management, not a deliberate suppression of ideas.
Fitness-beats-truth theorem shows perception is tuned for survival, not truth. If what we perceive is interface not reality, consciousness must be more fundamental than what it perceives.
Orch-OR proposes specific quantum mechanism in microtubules. Controversial but increasingly supported by Bandyopadhyay room-temperature quantum resonance findings.
If consciousness is the sole primitive, all mechanisms in the literature are necessarily modulation mechanisms — because there is nothing non-conscious to generate consciousness from.
Both frameworks hold consciousness as fundamental. Hoffman approaches from evolutionary theory and perception; Kastrup from analytic philosophy. Independent convergence on same ontological position.
